NJ Devil Comes to Visit Randall Carter

Randall Carter Elementary School was a part of the New Jersey Devils "Get Healthy" initiative. The school focused on the message about three goals they aim to hit every day: Be Educated, Be Healthy and Be Active. On April 4th, the New Jersey Devil, a mascot of the National Hockey League's New Jersey Devils, came to have fun and share a healthy message with Randall Carter students. The Devil also surprised students with a donation of new floor hockey equipment courtesy of the New Jersey Devils.

